has anyone else suffered with hyperemesis in pregnancy during the st months of my pregnancy i was terribly ill with hyperemesis and in and out of hospital all the time it was the most awful experience and i just wondered if anyone else had had the same thing x there is a help group that some suffers have put together just so you know your not alone blooming awful www hyperemesis org it stopped after months and i am currently weeks now im up and about feeling better but i still have to be very careful what i eat and im very funny with strong smells i hope you are felling better or will be feeling much better soon lots of love hang in there x mine lasted for months or so and it was the worst time in my life i wont lie i was told it was a sign of a healthy pregnancy though so that kind ofkept me going i was in and out of hospital adn was on a drip due to dehydration i am now weeks and days everyone is different in how long that they get it but once you are over it it is the best ever feeling in the world x Hyperemesis gravidarum Pregnancy Childbirth Marilyn Monroe Guinea pig EastEnders Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Diarrhea Clinical depression Menstrual cycle Abortion debate Days of our Lives Breastfeeding Something Awful Friends Social rule AFI 100 Years series Premature birth Theory of conduct Diabetes mellitus Fertility awareness Morning sickness Fitz Hugh Ludlow Miscarriage Stillbirth Cytomegalovirus Rei Ayanami Fasting Kodocha Psoriasis Anorexia nervosa Sant Thakar Singh Lake District Vomiting Postpartum depression Cindy Sheehan Time Out of Mind Laura Schlessinger Obstetrics Doxepin Kurt Cobain Melanie Wilkes Marathon (sport) She Loves You Simone Weil Abortion in the United States Infantilism John Howard Yoder Common cold Charles Darwin's illness History of As the World Turns (2000-present) Mojave people Limp Bizkit Knots Landing Abortion Medicine Lucille Ball Domestic rabbit End times Urinary incontinence Milton H. Erickson Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma 